00:18:16,728 --> 00:18:18,662
'Tis already changed.

232
00:18:35,047 --> 00:18:38,107
- Find anything?
- Maybe.

233
00:19:02,074 --> 00:19:04,167
So what are
those bookmarks then?

234
00:19:05,410 --> 00:19:07,344
Blanche writes about letters.

235
00:19:07,412 --> 00:19:10,404
Letters, letters that Christabel
wrote and received.

236
00:19:10,482 --> 00:19:12,507
And it nearly
drove Blanche crazy.

237
00:19:12,584 --> 00:19:14,518
Where are they?

238
00:19:14,586 --> 00:19:17,680
Lost. Destroyed. Who knows?
There's lots we haven't got.

239
00:19:17,756 --> 00:19:20,725
Not one of Blanche's
paintings has ever
turned up, for instance.

240
00:19:21,960 --> 00:19:23,894
So who do you think
wrote the letters?

241
00:19:23,962 --> 00:19:26,396
We've never been able
to verify who he was,

242
00:19:26,465 --> 00:19:28,865
but Ash certainly
isn't one of the candidates.

243
00:19:30,369 --> 00:19:33,167
You've got nothing.
I mean,
it's just a thought.

244
00:19:33,238 --> 00:19:35,172
Of course, I've thrown out
a lot of thoughts today,

245
00:19:35,240 --> 00:19:37,708
and you've pretty much
shot them all down, so...

246
00:19:37,776 --> 00:19:41,542
Yes, well,
it seems like a bit of
a wild-goose chase to me.

247
00:19:41,613 --> 00:19:43,547
I'd like to do
some more reading.

248
00:19:43,615 --> 00:19:47,051
I suppose you'll wish to
stay here overnight then?

249
00:19:47,119 --> 00:19:49,747
Well, I can't really afford
to stay overnight.

250
00:19:49,821 --> 00:19:52,722
Unless you want me huddled
downstairs in your doorway.

251
00:19:52,791 --> 00:19:55,692
I suppose I could put up
with you for one evening,
couldn't I?

252
00:20:04,803 --> 00:20:07,863
No doubt you know
Fergus Wolfe then.

253
00:20:07,940 --> 00:20:11,273
I'm sorry.
Uh, yeah, we're in
the same department.

254
00:20:11,343 --> 00:20:14,039
I imagine that
he told you that we're...

255
00:20:14,112 --> 00:20:16,046
occasionally
on together.

256
00:20:16,114 --> 00:20:20,778
- No, he didn't.
- Well, did he...

257
00:20:20,852 --> 00:20:24,219
Did he say anything...
about me?

258
00:20:24,289 --> 00:20:26,348
Uh...

259
00:20:27,259 --> 00:20:29,193
No.

260
00:20:31,597 --> 00:20:33,895
Right. I'll use
the bathroom first.
Get out of your way.

261
00:20:33,966 --> 00:20:37,060
Please. I'm just sort of
a brush and flush
kind of guy, so...

262
00:20:40,339 --> 00:20:42,466
Forget I said that.

263
00:20:42,541 --> 00:20:44,532
Maud.

264
00:20:44,610 --> 00:20:46,669
Can I show you something?

265
00:21:02,127 --> 00:21:04,095
Are these...
How did you get...
Those are the originals.

266
00:21:04,162 --> 00:21:06,096
I took them.
I sort of stole them.
Took them?

267
00:21:06,164 --> 00:21:08,132
Where from?
The London Library.

268
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:10,998
How could you do that?
It was on impulse.

269
00:21:11,069 --> 00:21:13,867
Impulse?

270
00:21:13,939 --> 00:21:16,271
Right. I've seen that
take-what-you-want attitude
in other...

271
00:21:16,341 --> 00:21:18,275
What, in other Americans?

272
00:21:18,343 --> 00:21:22,302
God, what is it with
you people and Americans?

273
00:21:22,381 --> 00:21:24,781
Look, I know that
I shouldn't have taken them.
I know that.

274
00:21:24,850 --> 00:21:27,080
But, Maud, I want to
find out what happened?

275
00:21:27,152 --> 00:21:28,983
Did he or didn't he
send the letter?

276
00:21:29,054 --> 00:21:30,988
You might not buy
into my theory,
but to me,

277
00:21:31,056 --> 00:21:33,183
Blanche's diary
suggests that it's possible.

278
00:21:33,258 --> 00:21:35,852
Wouldn't someone
have unearthed
a thing like this?

279
00:21:35,927 --> 00:21:39,226
- That's what makes it so big.
- Potentially so big.

280
00:21:39,298 --> 00:21:42,859
- Well, no one has.
- Probably because
those were never sent.

281
00:22:11,363 --> 00:22:13,593
Are you doing your homework?

282
00:22:14,833 --> 00:22:17,859
No, I'm just...
writing stuff.

283
00:22:17,936 --> 00:22:19,870
Stuff for me.
It's nothing.

284
00:22:19,938 --> 00:22:23,032
You're a closet poet.
Uh...

285
00:22:23,108 --> 00:22:25,576
more like basement,
really.

286
00:22:25,644 --> 00:22:28,238
I'm just, uh,
just fooling around.

287
00:22:28,313 --> 00:22:30,440
Is that what
you want to be
when you grow up?

288
00:22:30,515 --> 00:22:34,042
No, I'm gonna
be safe and teach
like everybody else.

289
00:22:35,954 --> 00:22:39,515
Besides,
there's no such thing
as poets anymore.

290
00:22:39,591 --> 00:22:43,027
Well... poet,

291
00:22:43,095 --> 00:22:47,293
do you want a secret
about his family home
before you go?

292
00:22:47,366 --> 00:22:50,062
Michell's late again.

293
00:22:52,270 --> 00:22:54,534
Roland asked for
another day off, Fergus.

294
00:22:54,606 --> 00:22:56,540
Oh, really?
Where's he gone?

295
00:22:56,608 --> 00:23:00,009
I didn't ask,
and he didn't say.

296
00:23:00,078 --> 00:23:03,536
He's American, for God's sake.
He's probably off
trafficking drugs.

297
00:23:03,615 --> 00:23:06,778
Did his new discovery
lead to anything?

298
00:23:06,852 --> 00:23:09,218
Ash's Vico.
Are you dreaming?

299
00:23:09,287 --> 00:23:13,280
Vico?
No, no, this had something
to do with Christabel LaMotte.

300
00:23:13,358 --> 00:23:16,759
He went to see
Dr. Bailey in Lincoln...
a woman.

301
00:23:16,828 --> 00:23:20,264
LaMotte. Hmm. No.

302
00:23:20,332 --> 00:23:23,267
- Well, it probably came
to nothing then.
- Exactly.

303
00:23:23,335 --> 00:23:25,895
Or he would have told you.

304
00:23:29,674 --> 00:23:31,665
Wouldn't he?

305
00:23:40,652 --> 00:23:43,143
Seal Court's
over there.

306
00:23:43,221 --> 00:23:45,951
So how long
did Christabel live at
this Seal Court place?

307
00:23:46,024 --> 00:23:49,152
Ages. The last 20
or so years of her life.

308
00:23:50,395 --> 00:23:52,329
Excuse me.
Sorry.

309
00:23:52,397 --> 00:23:55,798
"To a dusty shelf
we aspire."

310
00:23:57,869 --> 00:24:00,770
You should drop by Seal Court
before the train.

311
00:24:03,942 --> 00:24:07,002
And what do you do
in London, Mr. Michell?

312
00:24:07,078 --> 00:24:10,605
Are you a teacher as well?
No, not yet.
I'm doing a fellowship.

313
00:24:10,682 --> 00:24:14,482
- Which means what exactly?
- On the dole.

314
00:24:16,822 --> 00:24:19,120
Um, my field's
Victorian poetry.

315
00:24:19,191 --> 00:24:21,887
We had ourselves a poet
in this house once.

316
00:24:21,960 --> 00:24:26,624
Terrible, sentimental stuff
about God and death
and the dew and fairies.

317
00:24:26,698 --> 00:24:30,134
Why don't you show
this young man
Christabel's room, Maud?

318
00:24:30,202 --> 00:24:33,399
And why don't you
stay tonight?

319
00:24:34,806 --> 00:24:36,740
You're under no obligation
to stay, of course.

320
00:24:36,808 --> 00:24:39,402
It's justJoan's way.
Misses our daughter.

321
00:24:39,478 --> 00:24:41,776
Quite a drive back,
actually.
No, we're fine.

322
00:24:41,847 --> 00:24:43,838
Oh, well.

323
00:24:43,915 --> 00:24:46,509
Hardly ever come up here.

324
00:24:46,585 --> 00:24:51,215
With the wheelchair,
of course, we bunk down
on the ground floor.

325
00:24:56,561 --> 00:24:59,621
I haven't been up here
since I was a child.

326
00:25:02,501 --> 00:25:05,993
Maud, is this the photograph
at your house?

327
00:25:06,071 --> 00:25:08,232
Yes, that's
Christabel's niece, May.

328
00:25:08,306 --> 00:25:10,240
That's my
great-great-grandmother.

329
00:25:11,510 --> 00:25:15,276
Christabel wrote dozens of poems
about this place.

330
00:25:20,218 --> 00:25:24,712
"Haunted
are they who haunt our dreams
and weaken our desires...

331
00:25:24,789 --> 00:25:26,723
"and turn us
from a solid face.

332
00:25:26,791 --> 00:25:31,854
"And in the depth
of wintery night, they slumber
in the night and bright.

333
00:25:31,930 --> 00:25:36,697
"Dolly keeps a secret
safer than a friend.

334
00:25:36,768 --> 00:25:39,635
"Dolly's silent sympathy
lasts without end.

335
00:25:39,704 --> 00:25:43,800
"No rush of action,
this is our doom.

336
00:25:43,875 --> 00:25:48,812
To live a long life out
in a dark room. "

337
00:25:51,149 --> 00:25:53,777
Maud.

338
00:25:53,852 --> 00:25:55,911
It's pretty
incredible, huh?

339
00:26:03,862 --> 00:26:06,228
Fergus, it's me.

340
00:26:06,298 --> 00:26:10,325
l-I'm out of town tonight
on business.

341
00:26:10,402 --> 00:26:14,065
I've stumbled onto a connection
between Christabel
and Randolph Ash...

342
00:26:14,139 --> 00:26:16,073
and have a few questions
for you.

343
00:26:16,141 --> 00:26:21,443
Call me on 0 1 5-2263 2 4 1 6.

344
00:26:32,490 --> 00:26:34,549
Roland.

345
00:26:36,761 --> 00:26:39,389
- Roland.

346
00:26:39,464 --> 00:26:42,865
Roland. Roland.
No!

347
00:26:42,934 --> 00:26:46,131
Roland, it's me.
It's Maud.

348
00:26:47,439 --> 00:26:50,374
- What is it?
- Listen.

349
00:26:51,576 --> 00:26:55,273
" Dolly keeps a secret
safer than a friend.

350
00:26:55,347 --> 00:26:59,943
Dolly's silent sympathy
lasts without end. "

351
00:27:38,056 --> 00:27:40,456
God.

352
00:27:41,893 --> 00:27:43,986
I was so sure.

353
00:27:44,062 --> 00:27:47,691
Sympathy.
Sympathy.

354
00:27:47,766 --> 00:27:49,825
Sympathy, meaning what?

355
00:27:51,169 --> 00:27:53,194
Mutual affection
or understanding.

356
00:27:53,271 --> 00:27:57,469
Favor pity or even accord.
But that's not it, is it?

357
00:27:59,244 --> 00:28:01,178
That's what she told her.

358
00:28:02,681 --> 00:28:06,139
She uses silent sympathy
in a more classical context.

359
00:28:06,217 --> 00:28:09,345
Like structural support.
Dolly conceals it.

360
00:28:09,421 --> 00:28:12,913
Yes, but not within,
beneath.

361
00:28:19,030 --> 00:28:21,055
There's a door.
There's a door.

362
00:28:37,515 --> 00:28:39,608
- I can't believe it.
- Let me see.

363
00:28:39,684 --> 00:28:41,618
Be-Be careful.
They're very precious.
I'll be very careful.

364
00:28:41,686 --> 00:28:43,620
Oh, God, we shouldn't
be doing this.

365
00:28:43,688 --> 00:28:47,556
What do you mean,
we shouldn't be doing this?
Why'd you drag me up here then?

366
00:28:47,625 --> 00:28:49,820
What are you doing?
I'm going to read.

367
00:28:49,894 --> 00:28:51,828
Stop. We've got to
ask the Baileys.

368
00:28:51,896 --> 00:28:54,797
You ask,
and the next time you see these
is under glass in New Mexico.

369
00:28:54,866 --> 00:28:56,697
Stop it.
Stop. Stop. Stop.
All right. All right.

370
00:28:56,768 --> 00:28:58,736
But can we please
at least do it properly?

371
00:28:58,803 --> 00:29:01,237
Let me run downstairs
and get some note cards
and some pencils.

372
00:29:01,306 --> 00:29:03,433
All right.
Go, go! Hurry!

373
00:29:40,712 --> 00:29:42,873
Look at this. We've got
Ash and Christabel's
letters here.

374
00:29:42,947 --> 00:29:44,881
Look. Come here.
Listen.
What?

375
00:29:44,949 --> 00:29:47,645
"Dear Miss LaMotte:

376
00:29:47,719 --> 00:29:49,653
"It was a great pleasure
to talk to you...

377
00:29:49,721 --> 00:29:52,622
"at dear
Crabb-Robinson's party.

378
00:29:53,958 --> 00:29:56,859
" May I hope that you too
enjoyed our talk.

379
00:29:56,928 --> 00:30:00,329
And may I have the pleasure
of calling on you."

380
00:30:02,634 --> 00:30:06,001
She says, " No,
but you may write.

381
00:30:06,070 --> 00:30:10,063
"Would you rather
not have a letter,
however imperfect,

382
00:30:10,141 --> 00:30:13,110
"than a plate
of cucumber sandwiches,

383
00:30:13,178 --> 00:30:16,170
"however exquisitely
fine cut?

384
00:30:16,247 --> 00:30:19,011
Know you would,
and so would I. "

385
00:30:22,554 --> 00:30:27,218
 "I was entranced
and moved by your brief
portrait of your father. "

386
00:30:27,292 --> 00:30:30,193
"I write nonsense,
but if you can't write again,

387
00:30:30,261 --> 00:30:32,923
"you shall have a sober essay
on what you will.

388
00:30:32,997 --> 00:30:36,524
"Yours to command
in some things.

389
00:30:36,601 --> 00:30:38,535
"Where I was born,
Christabel Lamotte."

390
00:30:38,603 --> 00:30:40,798
"was a small place too.

391
00:30:40,872 --> 00:30:43,340
" Not like this.
Not bare.

392
00:30:43,408 --> 00:30:45,706
"A brilliant, dusty hutch
of mystery"...

393
00:30:45,777 --> 00:30:48,871
 Randolph]
is a cabinet of curiosities.

394
00:30:50,448 --> 00:30:52,916
What did my eyes
first light on?

395
00:30:52,984 --> 00:30:55,544
I am a creature of my pen.

396
00:30:55,620 --> 00:30:58,783
My pen is the best part
of me.

397
00:30:58,857 --> 00:31:01,621
I send you now
two more poems.

398
00:31:01,693 --> 00:31:04,753
I eagerly read
your mythic tales of mire...

399
00:31:04,829 --> 00:31:07,923
and found them
both charming and sad.

400
00:31:07,999 --> 00:31:12,026
Your verse is rich,
but perhaps the metaphor
is richer.

401
00:31:12,103 --> 00:31:14,037
Dear Mr. Ash:

402
00:31:14,105 --> 00:31:17,233
I live circumscribed
and self-communing.

403
00:31:17,308 --> 00:31:19,242
It is best so.

404
00:31:19,310 --> 00:31:23,474
Not like a princess
in the thicket, more like
a spider in her web.

405
00:31:23,548 --> 00:31:28,008
"Inclined to snap at visitors
or trespassers,

406
00:31:28,086 --> 00:31:31,647
"not perceiving the distinction
until too late.

407
00:31:31,723 --> 00:31:34,123
Thus, it is unwise to call. "

408
00:31:34,192 --> 00:31:36,558
I know you live very quietly.

409
00:31:36,628 --> 00:31:38,755
but I could be very quiet.

410
00:31:38,830 --> 00:31:41,264
I only want to discuss
Dante and Shakespeare,

411
00:31:41,332 --> 00:31:44,062
Wordsworth, Coleridge,
and Goethe.

412
00:31:44,135 --> 00:31:48,265
Not forgetting, of course,
Christabel LaMotte...

413
00:31:48,339 --> 00:31:51,672
and the ambitious
fairy project.

414
00:32:06,257 --> 00:32:09,488
 Christabel]
Oh, sir, things flicker
and shift.

415
00:32:09,560 --> 00:32:13,257
All spangle and sparkle
and flashes.

416
00:32:13,331 --> 00:32:16,789
I have sat all this long evening
by my fireside,

417
00:32:16,868 --> 00:32:19,632
turning towards
a caving in,

418
00:32:19,704 --> 00:32:22,138
the crumbling
of the consumed coals,

419
00:32:22,206 --> 00:32:25,004
to where I am leading myself...

420
00:32:25,076 --> 00:32:27,874
to lifeless dust, sir.

421
00:32:27,946 --> 00:32:33,646
My dear friend... for I may
call myself a friend, may I not?

422
00:32:35,019 --> 00:32:37,283
I speak to you as I would
speak to any person...

423
00:32:37,355 --> 00:32:40,552
who possesses my true thoughts.

424
00:32:40,625 --> 00:32:42,957
For my true thoughts
have spent more time
in your company...

425
00:32:43,027 --> 00:32:47,259
than in anyone else's
these last few weeks.

426
00:32:47,332 --> 00:32:49,800
Where my thoughts are,

427
00:32:49,867 --> 00:32:51,926
there am I in truth.

428
00:32:54,072 --> 00:32:57,701
"My dear friend:
It has been borne in upon me...

429
00:32:57,775 --> 00:33:01,643
that there are dangers
in our continued conversation."

430
00:33:01,713 --> 00:33:03,977
The world would not look well
upon letters...

431
00:33:04,048 --> 00:33:07,313
between a woman living
in shared solitude as I do...

432
00:33:07,385 --> 00:33:09,376
and a man.

433
00:33:09,454 --> 00:33:13,652
Even if that man
were a great poet.

434
00:33:13,725 --> 00:33:16,319
And if one is to live
in this way,

435
00:33:16,394 --> 00:33:20,797
it is imperative
to appear respectable
in the eyes of that world...

436
00:33:20,865 --> 00:33:23,060
and your wife.

437
00:33:24,569 --> 00:33:27,538
It is a sealed pact.

438
00:33:27,605 --> 00:33:31,439
It is a chosen way oflife
in which I have been
wondrously happy...

439
00:33:31,509 --> 00:33:34,740
and not alone in being so.

440
00:33:34,812 --> 00:33:37,542
"I have chosen a way,
dear friend,

441
00:33:37,615 --> 00:33:40,607
"I must hold to it.

442
00:33:40,685 --> 00:33:43,449
" Be patient.
Be generous. Forgive.

443
00:33:43,521 --> 00:33:48,424
"May I also request
that you return
my correspondence to me.

444
00:33:48,493 --> 00:33:52,122
"In this way,
at least our letters
will remain together.

445
00:33:52,196 --> 00:33:55,791
"I have known incandescence...

446
00:33:55,867 --> 00:33:58,768
"and must decline
to sample it any further.

447
00:34:00,104 --> 00:34:02,436
"This now goes to the post.

448
00:34:02,507 --> 00:34:06,238
Forgive its faults
and forgive me.
Christabel."

449
00:34:08,146 --> 00:34:10,637
My dear Christabel:

450
00:34:10,715 --> 00:34:13,616
Your letter came as a shock
to me, I will confess.

451
00:34:15,253 --> 00:34:20,156
I was at first
not only shocked, but angry
that you should write so.

452
00:34:21,993 --> 00:34:25,588
As you've asked about my wife,
however, I will tell you.

453
00:34:27,065 --> 00:34:30,125
I love Ellen,
but not as I love you.

454
00:34:32,904 --> 00:34:35,896
There are good reasons
which I cannot discuss
why my love for you...

455
00:34:35,973 --> 00:34:38,533
may not hurt her.

456
00:34:38,609 --> 00:34:41,635
I do not feel I have been
a proper wife to you, Randolph.

457
00:34:41,712 --> 00:34:44,237
Without children,
without ever
any kind of physical...

458
00:34:44,315 --> 00:34:46,749
Nonsense, Ellen.

459
00:34:46,818 --> 00:34:48,877
Nonsense.

460
00:34:50,588 --> 00:34:53,648
There are many
types of love.

461
00:34:54,859 --> 00:34:56,793
All sorts.

462
00:34:56,861 --> 00:35:02,458
And ours
are good between us.

463
00:35:04,836 --> 00:35:06,861
It has been most profound.

464
00:35:10,675 --> 00:35:13,337
 I must say to you
what is in my mind.

465
00:35:13,411 --> 00:35:16,642
I have called you my muse,
and so you are.

466
00:35:16,714 --> 00:35:19,706
I could call you
with even greater truth...

467
00:35:19,784 --> 00:35:22,309
my love.

468
00:35:22,520 --> 00:35:26,889
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
